This paper deals with the analysis of mobile app usage behavior and trends, which falls under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the impact of app usage behavior on user recommendations, which relates to Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper uses data mining and machine learning techniques to analyze app usage data, which falls under Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the manipulation of app download counts and user ratings, which relates to Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
